The paper presents a new class of directed graphical models for sequence modeling, which is a common topic in machine learning and natural language processing. The paper also applies the model to named entity recognition and web page classification tasks, which are subfields of natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
